        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">Calculated. Scaled from the global production volume using GDP.

The GDP of Europe without Switzerland in 2005 was 32.2% of the global GDP.

Global data are based on firewood and charcoal usage in developing nations of 1300 Mio m3 (UCS 2011), generic wood fuel ash content, and a generic global rate of 21.7w% of MSW going to incineration (Pike + UNSD 2012). Very uncertain figure, as firewood using nations tend to have little MSWI, so a global average calculation might be misleading.</productionVolumeComment>
